reviewText:
60 seconds from love to hate, from admiration to disappointment, from adventure's foretaste to boredom...

It's about:setting up priorities - what would you take to your fallout shelter ?;
managing resources - who will get food or/and water today ?;
wasteland exploration - someone must go and bring something useful;
random events and luck - even full-fed, completely hydrated man with an axe may not survive voyage to the surface (and this mothertrucker supposed to bring radio and food).
Why you should play this:unusual gameplay mechanic: you need to survive an atomic blast with limited resources (chosen or random), portion food and water, scavenge wasteland for useful items and supplies,
few game modes - you will find what meets your needs:
Apocalypse!" - you have some time to scavenge your home for resources and then evacuate yourself and family (or only yourself) to the shelter and try to survive untill the rescue mission;
"Scavenge" - some kind of a "fast-paced game": only scavenging your home for resources and evacuating to the shelter

